      "patterns": [
        "(?i)^cwe-schema$"
      ],
      "description": "CWE Schema (XSD) — versioned data format for the CWE catalog. Tracks the structural model independently of CWE content versions.",
      "weight": 100,
      "data": {
        "official_name": "CWE XML Schema Definition",
        "common_name": "CWE Schema",
        "alternate_names": [
          "CWE XSD"
        ],
        "description": "The XSD that defines the CWE data format — what fields exist on a weakness, how relationships are expressed, what attributes are required.",
        "notes": "CWE publishes two version numbers on independent tracks: the catalog/content version (e.g., 4.19.1) and the XSD schema version (e.g., 7.3). They are loosely coupled but not synchronized — a CWE major bump doesn't always mean an XSD major bump, and vice versa. Major XSD breaks: v5.0 → v6.0 was a structural rewrite (CWE 2.0 → 3.0), v6 → v7 added mapping/provenance infrastructure mid-CWE-4.x (with 4.12).",
        "version_required": false,
